course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-mustard-chicken-582c2691383a7f44a522dbd2
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(halved and cut into wedges) into wedges. Halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise and cut into ½-inch-thick half-moons) lengthwise, then cut into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Cut @sweet potatoes{12%oz}(cut into 1-inch cubes) into 1-inch cubes. Place veggies on a #baking sheet{}. Toss with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until tender and lightly browned, ~{25-35%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Whisk garlic, @honey{½%oz}, @whole grain mustard{1%tbsp}, @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}, and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season generously with @salt{generous amount} and @pepper{generous amount}. Stir to combine.

Place @chicken breasts{12%oz} in marinade and toss to coat.

Heat a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Remove chicken from marinade and sear in pan until no longer pink on outside, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Brush chicken with marinade as it cooks.

Once chicken is browned and sticky, pour over any remaining marinade. (TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, transfer chicken and marinade to a #baking dish{}.) With ~{8-10%minutes} to go on veggies, transfer pan with chicken to oven. Roast until chicken is firm and juices run clear when cut.

Divide chicken and veggies between #plates{}. Drizzle with any remaining sauce from pan. Tear leaves from @parsley{¼%oz}(leaves torn) and sprinkle on top.